<MediaContainer offset="0" totalSize="6" identifier="tv.plex.provider.epg" size="6"><Video art="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/widescreen/3840x2160/around_the_acl_16by9.jpg" guid="plex://movie/69f2a365ee86dfba6c875473" key="/library/metadata/69f2a365ee86dfba6c875473" ratingKey="69f2a365ee86dfba6c875473" summary="ATA 215: New Standings Shake-Up, Trust Battles, and Climb/Fall/Stay The standings just shifted—and Around the ACL is breaking down what actually matters. Meesh, Jake, and Anthony kick things off with the biggest surprises in the new rankings, including movement at the top with Colin Hodet holding #1 and pressure building behind him from Mark Richards, Zack Aiken, and Logan Chamberlain. Then, ACL National Director Todd Kisicki joins the show to talk about the ACL Europe Open in Croatia, the next Team USA mixed doubles qualifier, and what’s coming next for league structure. After that, it’s time to make some tough calls in “Who Do You Trust More?”—head-to-head decisions featuring names like Sammy Soto vs Gavin Cano and Matt Guy vs Jamie Graham. We close with Climb / Fall / Stay, predicting what’s next for key players in the standings. Who’s rising? Who’s slipping? And who’s right where they belong? Standings, strategy, and real decisions—this one sets the tone for what’s coming next." type="movie" contentRating="M/12" duration="3600000" originallyAvailableAt="2026-05-04T00:00:00Z" requiresConsent="1" skipParent="1" thumb="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/poster/2000x2858/around_the_acl_2by3.jpg" title="Around the ACL" userState="0" year="2026"><Image alt="Around the ACL" type="coverArt" url="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/widescreen/3840x2160/around_the_acl_16by9.jpg"/><Image alt="Around the ACL" type="coverPoster" url="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/poster/2000x2858/around_the_acl_2by3.jpg"/><Genre filter="genre=620143f98578b9238e1cdb8a" id="6